title.narrative: Orientation Visit - EGYPT, LEBANON AND MOROCCO RENEWABLE ENERGY ORIENTATION VISIT, through U.S. Energy Association

description.narrative: This $228,554 orientation visit (OV) brings delegates from Egypt, Lebanon and Morocco and one U.S. Embassy representative to the U.S. for ten days in order to evaluate U.S. solar, wind, and energy efficiency technologies. The objective of the OV is to familiarize members of the delegation with U.S. renewable energy technologies and facilitate business partnerships between U.S. companies and the public and private sectors of Egypt, Lebanon and Morocco.

title.narrative: Orientation Visit - JORDAN AND MOROCCO PORTS ORIENTATION VISIT, through Meridian International Center

description.narrative: This $244,773 orientation visit (OV) brings delegates from Jordan and Morocco and one member from the ongoing Morocco feasibility study contractor team to the U.S. for ten days in order to evaluate U.S. VTMS, IPCIS and ports security and surveillance technologies. The objective of this OV is to familiarize members of the delegation with these U.S. technologies and facilitate business partnerships between U.S. companies and the public sectors of Jordan and Morocco.

title.narrative: Orientation Visit - Maghreb Solar Reverse Trade Mission, through Millennium Science & Engineering, Inc.

description.narrative: This $266,828 Reverse Trade Mission (RTM) fosters the implemention of solar power projects in Morocco, Algeria, and Tunisia, and facilitates the participation of U.S. companies in the solar power sectors of these countries. The RTM delegation includes public and private sector representatives from Morocco, Algeria, and Tunisia's solar power sectors and one commercial Specialist. The RTM includes a business briefing, meetings with U.S. public and private sector representatives from the U.S. solar power sector, and relevant site visits.
